handleSubscriptionWebhook has no try/catch around the switch body. Any thrown error (invalid metadata, Stripe API 4xx, uncaught DB violation) propagates to the Hono onError which returns 500. Stripe then retries for 24h — disastrous for permanent errors.

The helper isTransientError() exists in workers/ecom-api/src/utils/error-classification.ts but is not used here. Same pattern issue in the other webhook handlers: subscription-webhook, checkout, payment-webhook, connect-webhook.

Site: workers/ecom-api/src/handlers/subscription-webhook.ts:94-204 (and audit other handlers)

Fix:
```typescript
try {
  switch (event.type) { ... }
} catch (err) {
  if (isTransientError(err)) {
    throw err; // 500 → Stripe retries
  }
  obs?.error('Permanent webhook error, acknowledging to prevent retries', {...});
  // let handler return 200 { received: true } via normal flow
}
```

Reference: skill backend-dev ref 06 §7 Permanent vs transient errors.

