2. MODIFY: apps/web/src/routes/(auth)/verify-email/+page.svelte (add resend option, improve states)

### Implementation Details

#### +page.server.ts
The verification should happen in the load function (server-side), NOT as a form action, because the user arrives via clicking an email link (GET request).

import { serverApiUrl } from '$lib/server/api';
import { COOKIES, getCookieConfig } from '@codex/constants';
import { extractSessionToken } from '$lib/server/auth-utils';
import { logger } from '$lib/observability';
import type { PageServerLoad } from './$types';

export const load: PageServerLoad = async ({ url, cookies, platform, request }) => {
  const token = url.searchParams.get('token');

  // No token — show pending state (user just registered, waiting for email)
  if (!token) {
    return { status: 'pending' as const };
  }

  try {
    // Call Auth Worker to verify email
    const authUrl = serverApiUrl(platform, 'auth');
    const res = await fetch(authUrl + '/api/auth/verify-email?token=' + encodeURIComponent(token), {
      method: 'GET',
      headers: {
        Cookie: cookies.get(COOKIES.SESSION_NAME)
          ? COOKIES.SESSION_NAME + '=' + cookies.get(COOKIES.SESSION_NAME)
          : '',
      },
    });

    if (!res.ok) {
      const error = await res.json().catch(() => ({}));
      return {
        status: 'error' as const,
        error: error.message || 'Invalid or expired verification link.',
      };
    }

    // Extract session token if BetterAuth auto-signs in
    const sessionToken = extractSessionToken(res);
    if (sessionToken) {
      const cookieConfig = getCookieConfig(platform?.env, request.headers.get('host') ?? undefined, {
        maxAge: COOKIES.SESSION_MAX_AGE,
      });
      cookies.set(COOKIES.SESSION_NAME, sessionToken, cookieConfig);
    }

    return { status: 'success' as const };
  } catch (err) {
    logger.error('Email verification error', { error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err) });
    return {
      status: 'error' as const,
      error: 'Something went wrong. Please try again.',
    };
  }
};

#### +page.svelte Enhancements
Modify the existing page to add:

1. A "Resend verification email" form action for expired tokens:
   - Show a button/link in the error state: "Resend verification email"
   - This calls a form action that POSTs to Auth Worker to resend
   - Requires an email input (or pass it via locals.user if authenticated)

2. Improved success state:
   - Show checkmark icon
   - "Email verified successfully! Redirecting to your library..."
   - Keep the existing onMount auto-redirect to /library after 3 seconds

3. Improved error state:
   - Show the error message from data.error
   - "Your verification link has expired or is invalid."
   - Resend button (if user provides email) or link to /login

4. Add a form action for resending:

// Add to +page.server.ts:
export const actions: Actions = {
  resend: async ({ request, platform }) => {
    const data = await request.formData();
    const email = data.get('email') as string;
    if (!email) return fail(400, { resendError: 'Email is required' });

    try {
      const authUrl = serverApiUrl(platform, 'auth');
      await fetch(authUrl + '/api/auth/email/send-verification-email', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ email }),
      });
    } catch { /* swallow */ }

    return { resent: true };
  },
};

### Auth Worker Endpoint Reference
- Verify: GET /api/auth/verify-email?token={token}
- Resend: POST /api/auth/email/send-verification-email with body { "email": "..." }
- Rate limit: 10 requests per 15 minutes per IP

### Acceptance Criteria
