executeTransfers catches every stripe.transfers.create error and immediately records as pendingPayouts(reason: 'transfer_failed'). A transient Stripe rate-limit or network error gets buried there and never retries — because the idempotencyKey marks the transfer 'done' on Stripe's side if it reached them, but our record says it failed.

Better: re-throw Stripe.errors.StripeConnectionError / StripeAPIError (transient) so Stripe's webhook retry can re-attempt the whole handler; only record permanent errors (StripeInvalidRequestError — bad destination, missing Connect, etc.) as pending payouts.

Sites in packages/subscription/src/services/subscription-service.ts:
- 1365-1388 (org fee transfer)
- 1455-1486 (creator payouts loop)
- 1538-1566 (single creator payout)

