Refactor all 11 studio pages from verbose onMount+$state+manual-loading pattern to modern SvelteKit remote function patterns per docs. Also fix bugs found in review.

Current anti-pattern (used in all pages):
```
let data = $state(null);
let loading = $state(true);
onMount(async () => {
  try { data = await remoteFunction(); }
  catch { data = null; }
  finally { loading = false; }
});
```

Target pattern (from SvelteKit remote function docs):
- Use query.loading / query.current / query.error properties
- OR use $derived(await query(arg)) with <svelte:boundary> for loading/error
- Eliminate manual loading flags entirely
- Use query.refresh() for re-fetch instead of manual fetchData() functions

Bugs to fix:
1. Customers page: missing $effect watching URL params — pagination clicks don't re-fetch
2. Role guards inconsistency: some pages use $effect+goto, some don't guard at all

Ref: docs/review/ux-caching-tanstack-research.md, SvelteKit Remote Functions docs

Surfaced by Codex-fxc6f grep pass. Different bug class from qt5w/fxc6f (which fixed multiplicative decay). Here the pattern is counter-based fixed lifespan:

- apps/web/src/lib/components/ui/ShaderHero/renderers/lenia-renderer.ts:237-238 — 'clickBursts[i].frame++' with 'mStr = 0.6 * (1.0 - b.frame / 5.0)' (5-frame linear decay)
- apps/web/src/lib/components/ui/ShaderHero/renderers/suture-renderer.ts:724 — identical 'b.frame++' inside a clickBursts loop, same 5-frame lifespan

On 120Hz displays a click visually lasts 5/120 = 42ms; on 60Hz it lasts 5/60 = 83ms; on throttled 30Hz it lasts 167ms. Same frame-rate-dependence bug class as qt5w/fxc6f, but different fix pattern.

Fix: replace the frame counter with elapsed-seconds counter:

  // Instead of: b.frame++; mStr = 0.6 * (1.0 - b.frame / 5.0);
  b.age += dt;
  mStr = 0.6 * Math.max(0, 1 - b.age / BURST_LIFETIME_SECONDS);
  // Remove bursts where b.age >= BURST_LIFETIME_SECONDS

Target lifespan in seconds: 5/60 = 0.0833s. Make it a module-level const (BURST_LIFETIME_SECONDS = 5 / 60) with a comment explaining the 60fps-equivalent tuning.

Implementation notes:
- Needs dt threaded the same way mycelium-renderer now does it (lastTime instance state in render(), dt clamped to 0.1s, reset on preset switch / pause resume).
- clickBursts shape will need 'age: number' field replacing or alongside 'frame: number'. Prefer replace (narrow API surface).
- Consider extracting a small clickBursts utility to shared location if both renderers converge on identical logic.
- Reference: commit 6515674b for the elapsed-time dt pattern.

