Iter-021 Agent G surfaced a minor noise issue while auditing hero visibility.

ROOT:
apps/web/src/lib/brand-editor/css-injection.ts:466-473 injectBrandVars loops over state.tokenOverrides and writes CSS custom properties for each key. The emission uses BRAND_PREFIX_KEYS to decide whether the key maps to --brand-* (a few specific keys) or --color-* (everything else).

hero-hide-* keys are NOT in BRAND_PREFIX_KEYS, so they emit as --color-hero-hide-title: 1, --color-hero-hide-stats: 1, etc.

NO CONSUMER READS THESE:
- org-brand.css doesn't reference --color-hero-hide-*
- +page.svelte:2299-2326 uses data-hero-hide-* ATTRIBUTES (not CSS vars)
- Grep confirms zero var(--color-hero-hide-*) references across apps/web/

SYMPTOM:
During editor preview sessions, .org-layout's inline style attribute accumulates useless CSS custom properties. Not a functional bug — the hide behavior works correctly via attributes — but noise in dev tools and a slight memory footprint.

FIX:
Add a skip-set or prefix filter in injectBrandVars:

  const ATTRIBUTE_ONLY_KEYS = new Set(['hero-hide-title', 'hero-hide-logo', 'hero-hide-description', 'hero-hide-pills', 'hero-hide-stats']);
  // Alternative: if (key.startsWith('hero-hide-')) continue;

for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(state.tokenOverrides ?? {})) {
  if (ATTRIBUTE_ONLY_KEYS.has(key)) continue;
  // ... rest of injection logic
}

Prefer the prefix check: it's future-proof if more attribute-only keys are added (e.g. data-hero-*, data-layout-*).

