## Security Considerations
- NEVER use eval() or new Function()
- NEVER use Handlebars/Mustache (potential RCE)
- Always escape HTML in values
- Whitelist tokens per template type
- Unknown tokens become empty (don't leak)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] escapeHtml prevents XSS
- [ ] renderTemplate replaces {{tokens}} with data
- [ ] Unknown tokens become empty (logged)
- [ ] Missing tokens become empty (logged)
- [ ] Token registry defines allowed tokens per template
- [ ] Tests cover escaping, missing, unknown scenarios
- [ ] No third-party template libraries used

## Problem

Several server loaders call `setHeaders(CACHE_HEADERS.DYNAMIC_PUBLIC)` BEFORE their data fetches. If the fetch throws, the resulting 4xx/5xx error response inherits `cache-control: public, max-age=300, s-maxage=300, stale-while-revalidate=3600`, and CDNs happily serve the cached error to every subsequent visitor for 5 minutes.

Discovered while fixing the `/explore?creator=<username>` Bad Request bug: the 400 response came back with a 5-minute public cache header, which would have poisoned the CDN if deployed. Example repro (before fix): stale cached 400 page persisted in the browser until hard-reload.

## Affected files (initial scan — verify each)

- `apps/web/src/routes/_creators/[username]/content/+page.server.ts:22`
- `apps/web/src/routes/_creators/[username]/+page.server.ts:22`
- `apps/web/src/routes/_org/[slug]/(space)/creators/+page.server.ts:15`
- Any other `+page.server.ts` that calls `setHeaders(CACHE_HEADERS.DYNAMIC_PUBLIC | STATIC_PUBLIC)` before an `await` that could throw

Already fixed in this session:
- `apps/web/src/routes/_org/[slug]/(space)/explore/+page.server.ts` — moved `setHeaders` to AFTER the fetch in both branches

## Rule

`setHeaders(CACHE_HEADERS.DYNAMIC_PUBLIC)` and `STATIC_PUBLIC` MUST be called only after every `await` that could throw has succeeded. PRIVATE is safe to call anywhere (its whole purpose is to opt OUT of caching, which also correctly applies to error responses).

## Fix pattern

```ts
// Before — error path picks up public cache
export const load: PageServerLoad = async ({ setHeaders, ... }) => {
  setHeaders(CACHE_HEADERS.DYNAMIC_PUBLIC);
  const data = await thingThatCanThrow();
  return { data };
};

// After — only successful responses get the cache policy
export const load: PageServerLoad = async ({ setHeaders, ... }) => {
  const data = await thingThatCanThrow();
  setHeaders(CACHE_HEADERS.DYNAMIC_PUBLIC);
  return { data };
};
```

## Acceptance

- [ ] All public-cache `setHeaders` calls moved to after successful fetches
- [ ] Manually verify 4xx/5xx responses on each affected page return `cache-control: no-cache` (default) or PRIVATE, not `public, max-age=300`
- [ ] Document the rule in `apps/web/CLAUDE.md` under the HTTP Cache Headers section

